# Digital Fingerprinting Framework for Threat Assessment

**Author:** Aetherverse Intelligence Protocol  
**Purpose:** Open-source intelligence framework for security professionals conducting authorized threat assessments  
**Focus:** Digital footprint mapping, attack surface discovery, and threat correlation  
**Status:** v1.0 — Production-ready methodology

---

## 🎯 Overview

This framework provides a structured approach to digital fingerprinting for threat assessments. It combines multiple OSINT disciplines into a cohesive workflow, enabling security teams to build comprehensive threat profiles of individuals, organizations, and infrastructure.

**Key Differentiators:**
- Multi-layered intelligence gathering (7 domains)
- Cross-platform correlation & identity mapping
- Automated threat scoring & risk prioritization
- Graph-based relationship visualization
- AI-assisted false-positive reduction

---

## 🏗️ Framework Architecture

```

┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                    INPUT LAYER                          │
│  Domain │ IP │ Username │ Email │ Name │ Company      │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
│
▼
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
