## 📊 Output Examples

### Sample Threat Profile
```

TARGET: techstartup.io
────────────────────────────────────────────
INFRASTRUCTURE:
• IP: 192.0.2.45 (AWS us-east-1)
• Subdomains: 23 discovered (api, dev, staging, admin...)
• TLS: Valid cert (Let's Encrypt), weak ciphers detected
• Open Ports: 22, 80, 443, 3306 (MySQL exposed)

TECHNOLOGY:
• nginx/1.18.0, PHP/7.4.33, WordPress 5.8.2
• Cloudflare WAF detected

IDENTITY:
• Emails found: 47 (25 employees, 12 external)
• Usernames matched: 18 across 45 platforms
• Breach exposure: 3 records in 2 breaches

THREAT SCORE: HIGH
⚠️  MySQL exposed on port 3306
⚠️  WordPress version 5.8.2 (vulnerable)
⚠️  Admin panel exposed: /wp-admin
⚠️  Employee credentials in 2023 data breach

RECOMMENDATIONS:
• Restrict MySQL to internal networks
• Update WordPress to latest version
• Implement MFA for all employees

```

